<HEADLINE>
Tons of treasure, what to buy?
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<POST>
<POSTER> "Peter" &lt;pmara...@gmail.com&gt; </POSTER>
<POSTDATE> 2007-01-19T23:09:00 </POSTDATE>
I just realized that I have a kind of urgent question (I'm playing
tomorrow). My party has won a huge amount of treasure - more than we
ever expected to get - and now we need to make up wish lists of magic
items to buy. Not everything will be available, but a lot will be - I
hope.

We're playing in the Forgotten Realms, in Cormyr. I'm playing a
7th-level cleric of Tymora, CG. I cast Fly daily, wear very heavy
magical platemail (+1, lesser fortification, Silent Moves), and have a
+1 cloak of resistance. I get into combat pretty often.

Oh, and I also have a +1 steel shield.

Obviously I'll want a periapt of wisdom (as high as possible), a pearl
of power (ditto), and a +1 or better weapon. What else would you put on
your wish list in my situation? I don't have a GP count, but it's very,
very high.

I'd appreciate any suggestions...

-&gt;Peter

--
