A rod of metamagic, preferably Quicken.  Even if it's only the lesser,
limited to 3rd level spells or below, my cleric had one last campaign
and it proved very useful, not just for a Quicken Divine Favor/Divine
Power.

However, especially since you just took Extend Spell for those 3.0
ability buff spells, more valueable to you would be a rod of Empower or
even better a rod of Maximize.  With a rod of Maximize on your Extended
Bull's Strength that's +5 strength for 14 hours, guaranteed.  If you
take rod of Empower, you get a range of +3 to +7 depending on your
roll.  The Maximize rod is more efficient.  Also use it on an Extended
Endurance Spell for +5 Consitution for 14 hours a day.

Definitely, a rod of Maximize.

Gerald Katz
