A better cloak. Even as a cleric, your saves can never be too high.

<QUOTE PREVIOUSPOST="
&gt; I get into combat pretty often.
">

A +1 holy weapon, season to taste with bane if you find yourself
fighting a single creature type (or is bane +2 in 3.0?), elemental
enhacements... not straight plusses, since you can get those easily
enough through greater magic weapon.

<QUOTE PREVIOUSPOST="
&gt; Obviously I'll want a periapt of wisdom (as high as possible),
">

Right. But not too high: if you've got something like 50,000 gp to
spend, you're better of with (for example) a periapt +4, +1 holy weapon
and +1 moderater fortification armour than with a periapt +6 and the
armour, but no weapon.

As a general rule: don't spend it all in one place. :)

<QUOTE PREVIOUSPOST="
&gt; a pearl of power (ditto),
">

Not necessarily. Low-level pearls of power are great when you're low
level (when you've got three 1st-level spells, another one is +33%
capacity!), but at high levels, they get prohibitively expensive. I
wouldn't bother with a pearl of power past 3rd level or so.

<QUOTE PREVIOUSPOST="
&gt; What else would you put on
&gt; your wish list in my situation? I don't have a GP count, but it's very,
&gt; very high.
">

A necklace of prayer beads that contains a bead of karma (you'll have to
check the specifics, I think there has been some changes 3.0-&gt;3.5). It
lets you boost your caster level by +4 for 10 minutes. Do it at the
start of the day, and get even better enhancements from magic vestment
and greater magic weapon, and they (and bull's stregth &amp;c.) last 4 hours
longer.

But again, if the necklace is more than, say, a third of your spending
money, it's probably not worth it.

--
